<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-31T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On October 24 President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>
                                proclaimed that the state of war between the United States and the
                                Government of Germany had been terminated on October 19. For the
                                text of the proclamation, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign
                                    Policy, 1950–1955: Basic Documents</hi>, volume II, pages
                                1723–1724, or 66 Stat. c3.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>